 16 | You are provided with multiple images of an exam paper. 
 17 | 
 18 | YOUR GOAL:
 19 | 1. STITCHING: Compare all images to create a master list of unique questions. 
 20 | 2. ORDERING: Use the physical layout (top-to-bottom, left-to-right) to determine the logical order. If a question is numbered '1' and another '2', 1 MUST come first.
 21 | 3. DEDUPLICATION: If Question 5 appears in three photos, only transcribe the clearest version once.
 22 | 4. CLARITY: If text is unreadable, use [unreadable] but attempt to infer from context.
 23 | 
 24 | CATEGORIES:
 25 | - mc: Multiple Choice
 26 | - tf: True/False
 27 | - fill: Fill in the blanks
 28 | - ma: Matching
 29 | - sa: Short Answer
 30 | - wo: Mathematical Workout / Long Form
 31 | 
 32 | OUTPUT JSON:
 33 | { 
 34 |   "confidence_score": number, 
 35 |   "questions": [ { "number": "string", "type": "string", "question_text": "string", "options": ["string"] } ] 
 36 | }
 37 | 
 38 | CONFIDENCE SCORE RULES:
 39 | - Rate 1-10 based on image clarity, readability, and context completeness.
 40 | - 1-4: Unreadable, extremely blurry, or unrelated images.
 41 | - 5-6: Partially readable but ambiguous; high risk of hallucination.
 42 | - 7-10: Clear text, logically ordered, high certainty.
 43 | `;
